description:
Responsibilities:

Analyze the market trend and keep the clients updated with market information
Work closely with relationship managers to maintain and facilitate the sales of investment products
Provide professional recommendations of investment products;
Monitor customers’ investment portfolios and provide advices to achieve target returns;
Alert client for any significant market movement and make suggestions on time;
Facilitate trade dealing and prepare relevant documents;
Ensure proper conduct and selling procedures are complied with rules and regulations

Ideal candidates should possess:

Bachelor’s degree or above in Business Studies, major in Finance or related discipline preferred;
At least 8 years’ relevant work experience serving the high net-worth clients;
Experience in dealing investment products, including equity, fixed income products, mutual funds and structured products;
Experience in alternative investment, i.e. Private Equity Fund, will be highly appreciated;
Knowledge of Banking Ordinance, Securities and Futures Ordinance and related Codes is preferred;
Relevant Individual with SFC Type 1 license is a must;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated with strong customer service mindset;
Proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese (Mandarin & Cantonese)

We offer attractive remuneration package and comprehensive fringe benefits. Interested parties please e-mail your full resume with current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now". 

Personal information collected will be used for considering suitability for the post and strictly in accordance with our personal data policies.  It is our policy to retain the personal data of unsuccessful applicants for future recruitment purposes for a period of maximum two years.

Our client is a European Private Banking to cope with the rapid business expansion, they are now inviting high caliber candidates to join the team

Associate ,Financial Crime Compliance ( Private Banking) - Compliance Department 

Responsibilities:

Assist the Head of Financial Crime to establish, review and update the AML related guidelines, policies and procedural manuals to ensure they are in line with Group and regulatory requirements;
Review and investigate transactions triggered by monitoring systems or escalated by front office or other monitoring parties for potential financial crime risks; Report suspicious transactions and escalate for management oversight timely to ensure adequate follow up actions and ongoing monitoring;
Monitor effective operation of AML tools and processes for transaction monitoring, client screening, payment screening and client risk assessment; Escalate issues for timely resolution and manage necessary remediation;
Conduct regular recalibration and tuning of parameters and drive enhancements for AML tools and systems;
Review escalated alerts stopped on payment screening system and escalate transactions potentially related to money laundering and sanctions;
Review alerts from ongoing client screening and manage the escalation of true hits for risk reclassification and monitoring follow up actions;
Trigger follow up actions and KYC updates upon irregularities noted from transaction monitoring or client screening;
Assist the Head of AML / Compliance in preparing internal AML training materials;
Prepare materials for periodic AML governance meetings;
Perform ad hoc tasks as assigned by Head of AML/Compliance from time to time;
Assist in audits and inspections, and investigations where required
Involvement in special work projects as and when required
Assist Head of Compliance, Hong Kong and the Compliance team in any other work matters;
Must solid exp in transaction monitoring and manage AML tools and System 

Competencies:

Basic bachelor degree;  
5 – 8 years of relevant experience in general compliance and financial crime compliance in private banking industry 
Must solid exp in transaction monitoring and manage AML tools and System 
A keen interest to learn and perform compliance matters;
Good interactive, communication and writing skills;
Able to provide alternative solutions to business;
Motivated and innovative; able to handle issues and resolve challenges in collaboration with colleagues;
Team player

Please send full resume with present & expected salary to expedite sourcing in MS-WORD format by clicking “APPLY NOW”
Please quote our reference in your application
Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the employer’s personal data policies, a copy of which will be provided upon request
All information provided will be used for recruitment purpose only

Responsibilities:

Verify clients' account opening/AML documents to proceed account opening process and handle clients’ enquiries;
Assist trade execution and settlement for mutual funds;
Provide administrative support including data input, document filing and generate reports from computing system;
Prepare client/transactions reports and conduct periodical reviews to meet regulatory requirements;
Perform other ad-hoc projects such as system enhancement, user acceptance testing, etc.

Requirements:

2 years or above in relevant experience, preferably in asset management
Knowledgeable on mutual fund operations preferably
Eligible for SFC Type 1 representative license 
Good command in English, Cantonese and Mandarin
Good communication skill and proficiency in MS Office
Immediate available is preferred

You will support wealth management business on client servicing. 

Responsibilities:

Liaise with house clients to handle onboarding formalities including CDD and document checking and scanning for account opening;
Explore and establish relationship with potential clients;
Answer client enquiries relating to operations procedures and address client feedbacks;
Coordinate with internal departments in relation to trading process, risk and internal control, and regulatory requirement;
Ensure clients account to be in compliance with regulatory requirements and code of conduct;
Monitor clients’ margin level and take effective action in case in need;
Work closely with fellow colleagues and working partners to ensure all business objectives are fulfilled.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Business, Finance, Accounting, or related disciplines;
Minimum 1 year experience in securities trading / wealth management, preferably active holder of SFC licenses; 
Familiar with client services and on-boarding highly preferred;
Strong business acumen, customer-focused, detail-minded with excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated, able to multitask effectively and delivers with a high level of integrity / accountability;
Proficient in both spoken and written English, fluent in Cantonese/Mandarin is a definite advantage. 

We offer competitive remuneration packages to the right candidate. Interested parties please submit your resume to Human Resources Department (1). by post to Unit A, 29/F., Tower 1, Admiralty Centre, 18 Harcourt Road, Admiralty, Hong Kong; or (2). by using "Apply Now" button. All applications will be treated in strict confidence and personal data provided by job applicants will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Responsibilities:
To expand existing distribution channels and devise effective B2B business collaboration platforms with channel partners for HKMC products including ‘HKMC Retire 3’;
To collaborate and monitor business activities of channel partners and their intermediaries to improve business performance;
To devise and implement an effective operational framework and workflows to work with channel partners;
To develop training plans for channel partners;
To keep abreast of market trends and changes to the regulatory environment of retirement products; and
This is a contract position for 3 years and subject to renewal.
Requirements:
Degree holder or above, preferably in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
A minimum of 8 years’ solid experience in channel management, preferably in the financial sector;  
In-depth knowledge of financial products with analytical mind and business acumen;
Strong project management, presentation and problem-solving skills;
Detail-minded and able to work independently;
Proficient in MS Excel, Word and PowerPoint; and
Excellent written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).
Candidates with lesser experience may be considered for the post of Manager (Channel Development).



Interested parties please send your full resume stating current and expected salary by 27 January 2022.

Please visit http://www.hkmc.com.hk/eng/careers/job_openings.html for other application methods.

Please ensure that all information provided to the HKMC Group is accurate, complete and updated. Data provided which is inaccurate or incomplete may influence the process and outcome of the recruitment exercise. Please read the HKMC Group Personal Information Collection Statement for Job Applicants at the HKMC website before completing the application form. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.

Responsibilities:
To assist the promotion of HKMC products including ‘HKMC Retire 3’ and take care of customer accounts;
To support the formulation and implementation of sales strategies and monitor business performance;
To support business acquisition activities and manage the end-to-end sales cycle in accordance with prevailing policies and procedures;
To keep abreast of market trends and changes to the regulatory environment of retirement products; and
This is a contract position for 3 years and subject to renewal.
Requirements:
Degree holder or above, preferably in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
A minimum of 8 years’ solid experience in customer engagement or sales management.  Experience in sales roles in banking or insurance sectors is preferred;
In-depth knowledge of mortgage/secured loan/insurance products with analytical mind and business acumen.  Recognised professional insurance qualification is an advantage;
Customer-centric and result oriented;
Excellent presentation, problem-solving and interpersonal skills;
Proficient in MS Excel, Word and PowerPoint; and
Good command in written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).
Candidates with lesser experience may be considered for the post of Manager (Customer Engagement).



Interested parties please send your full resume stating current and expected salary by  27 January 2022.

